'''Given n non-negative integers representing an elevation map where the width of each bar is 1, compute how much water it can trap after raining.1) two pointers method to keep track on left and right max bar heights2) If leftMax is lower, advance left pointer, and if rightMax is lower, advance right pointer.3) calcuate the trapped water at each ber(index) and add to the total water area.4) update left or right max based on current bar height.5)repeat until pointers meet.'''height = [0,1,0,2,1,0,1,3,2,1,2,1]left_ind=0right_ind=len(height)-1left_max_height=height[left_ind]right_max_height=height[right_ind]water_area=0while left_ind<right_ind:        if left_max_height <right_max_height:                left_ind+=1        left_max_height=max(left_max_height,height[left_ind])        water_area+=left_max_height-height[left_ind]            else:         right_ind -=1         right_max_height=max(right_max_height,height[right_ind])         water_area+=right_max_height-height[right_ind]                  print("trapped water",water_area)